660	For any linear code, any line, and every $S\subseteq D$: at most one $z$ is bad with witness $S$, at any radius.  Hence $\emca(C,\delta)\le\#\{S:\ |S|\ge(1-\delta)n,\ C|_S\ne\F^S\}/q\le2^n/q$, and if $q\ge2^n/\eps^*$ then $\delta^*_C(\eps^*)=1$ exactly: over very large fields the no-slack principle holds trivially, for every line.
661	\end{theorem}
